This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommending item lists to users. It also involves modeling user preferences and item consistency, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of self-attentive aggregation layers suggests a focus on neural networks and deep learning (cs.SI), while the availability of code and data indicates a potential interest in computational methods (cs.CY).
